name: Stark County Health Department
tweet: As we approach Thanksgiving, here is where Stark County stands with those that have at least 1 dose of a COVID-19 vaccine and those fully vaccinated. Residents with an additional dose (18+) stands at 15% of the eligible population. Stay safe and healthy this holiday season!  https://t.co/c1i1W85ZwS

name: Stark County Health Department
tweet: We have 5 doses of Pfizer for ages 5-11 and 2 doses for those 12 years of age and older. If you can be at our health department before 4:15 PM, please call 330.492.1681. We are located in the Park Centre Plaza at 7235 Whipple Ave. NW in North Canton.

name: Stark County Health Department
tweet: Can you mix and match at one of our clinics? Yes, you can. Our health department offers Moderna and Pfizer only. Johnson & Johnson providers can be found at  https://t.co/KZECUzJJbe. Learn more about the process and boosters at  https://t.co/SCe09YOq0B.  https://t.co/zII7gbcuxG

name: Stark County Health Department
tweet: Eligibility for boosters has been extended to all those residents that are 18 years of age and older. You must have received you 2nd dose 6 months ago or your only dose of Johnson & Johnson 2 months ago. Schedule at  https://t.co/dIhFG0wfVg for an appointment!  https://t.co/LOEvsADQTL

tweet: We are hosting our Tot Tuesday COVID-19 Vaccine clinic for those 5-11 years old at our health department.
